IBM, Intel to Invest $4 Billion in Albany Nanotechnology Deal

-- B y   F r e e m a n   K l o p o t t
-- 
2011-09-27T13:52:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/ibm-intel-to-invest-4-billion-nanotechnology-investment-at-albany-school.html
International Business Machines
Corp. (IBM)  and  Intel Corp. (INTC)  will invest $4 billion in a nanotechnology
venture in Albany, said a spokesman for New York Governor  Andrew
Cuomo .  Cuomo will announce the investment today, said the
spokesman, Stephen Morello, in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Freeman Klopott in Albany at 
 fklopott@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
